result.execSummary:
The defendant Corey D Brown was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Corey D Brown in court with attorney Robert L. Taylor.  Defendant Corey D Brown in custody.  Nicolas J. Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Courts finds that State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.    

AS TO COUNT #1: Court ordered defendant to serve 29 days (CONSECUTIVE to count #2 and case 2014CF2329), in the House of Correction, with 29 days credit for time served.  TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.  Costs and fees to be paid as a condition of probation under (count #2) and case 2014CF2329.    

AS TO COUNT #2: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS (CONCURRENT to case 2014CF2329), with credit for 0 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR.  The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions:  
* Court ordered the defendant to serve 60 DAYS
   in the House of Correction.  Stayed pending review.
* Successfully complete "Batterers intervention"
   counseling and continue programming.
* Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment
   and successfully complete recommended treatment.
* Random urine screens and breathalyzer test.
* Maintain absolute sobriety.  No drugs.  No alcohol.
* Successfully complete any other counseling and/or
   treatment deemed appropriate.
* No contact with victim, Tynecha Br., 
   without prior court approval.  
* Obtain and maintain employment.
* No firearms; weapons.
* Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges,
   victim/witness surcharge, the domestic violence
   surcharge, and supervision fees as determined by
   the Department of Corrections, during period of probation or CIVIL JUDGMENT.
    - costs and fees also apply to count #1 (case 2014CF984).  
* Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
* Restitution is set at zero.
**COURT ORDERED PROBATION REVIEW HEARING IN BR. 4 on 2-6-2015 AT 1:30 PM.
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.
